title: 'Worth considering- But (Not Perfect)'
body: If you're looking for intense pigmentation this eyeliner delivers. The true matte finish in rich shades adds a touch of elegance to any look.  However, there were a few drawbacks. The quick-dry feature sometimes does not perform for me as I have hooded eyes. And it is challenging to correct it when it happens. Additionally, the flexible tip, while offering control, felt flimsy at times.  On the bright side, it stayed put throughout the day without smudging, perfect for busy schedules. Yet, if you're a beginner, achieving precise lines may take practice.  In conclusion, the SUGAR POP eyeliner is decent, but not without flaws. If you prioritize long-lasting wear and pigmentation, it's worth considering.
